"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-03-28-paris-2024-super-falcons-goalie-nnadozie-targets-olympics-qualification\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Super Falcons goalkeeper, Chiamaka Nnadozie is keen to make an appearance at the 2024 Olympic Games.  Nine-time African champions, Super Falcons last featured at the Olympics 16 years ago.  Nnadozie was part of the team that failed to qualify for the last edition of the games in Tokyo, Japan.  Randy Waldrum's side will have to overcome reigning African champions South Africa over a two-legged fixture next month to make it to Paris 2024.  \\\"I read so many things about the Olympics. We did not manage to qualify in 2020, I felt bad at first, then I said to myself 'Come on, you have time ahead of you' and that it is another great opportunity to qualify,\\\" Nnadozie told CAFonline.  \\\"I want to know what it feels like to participate in the Olympic Games.\\\"  Matthew commends Remo Stars Ladies' players despite defeat to Bayelsa Queens  EPL: Chelsea midfielder ready to leave Pochettino's side  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Friendly: Babajide relishes Super Falcons' win over Cameroon  Friendly: Super Falcons floor Cameroon 3-1 in Yaounde  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"